verses.text_plain: Give ear, O Shepherd of Israel, thou that leadest Joseph like a flock; thou that dwellest between the cherubims, shine forth.
verses.verse_html:
1Give ear, O Shepherd of Israel, thou that leadest Joseph like a flock; thou that dwellest between the cherubims, shine forth. ▼
▼ of: or, for

verses.text_plain: Before Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh stir up thy strength, and come and save us.
verses.verse_html:
2Before Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh stir up thy strength, and come and save us. ▼
▼ come…: Heb. come for salvation to us

footnotes.body_text: ▼ come…: Heb. come for salvation to us
footnotes.body_html: ▼ come…: Heb. come for salvation to us

verses.text_plain: Turn us again, O God, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.
verses.verse_html: 3Turn us again, O God, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.

verses.text_plain: O Lord God of hosts, how long wilt thou be angry against the prayer of thy people?
verses.verse_html:
4O Lord God of hosts, how long wilt thou be angry against the prayer of thy people? ▼
▼ be…: Heb. smoke

tokens.text: how long wilt thou be angry

verses.text_plain: Thou feedest them with the bread of tears; and givest them tears to drink in great measure.
verses.verse_html: 5Thou feedest them with the bread of tears; and givest them tears to drink in great measure.

verses.text_plain: Thou makest us a strife unto our neighbours: and our enemies laugh among themselves.
verses.verse_html: 6Thou makest us a strife unto our neighbours: and our enemies laugh among themselves.

verses.text_plain: Turn us again, O God of hosts, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.
verses.verse_html: 7Turn us again, O God of hosts, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast brought a vine out of Egypt: thou hast cast out the heathen, and planted it.
verses.verse_html: 8Thou hast brought a vine out of Egypt: thou hast cast out the heathen, and planted it.

verses.text_plain: Thou preparedst room before it, and didst cause it to take deep root, and it filled the land.
verses.verse_html: 9Thou preparedst room before it, and didst cause it to take deep root, and it filled the land.

tokens.text: it, and didst cause it to take deep

verses.text_plain: The hills were covered with the shadow of it, and the boughs thereof were like the goodly cedars.
verses.verse_html:
10The hills were covered with the shadow of it, and the boughs thereof were like the goodly cedars. ▼
▼ goodly…: Heb. cedars of God

footnotes.body_html: ▼ goodly…: Heb. cedars of God

verses.text_plain: She sent out her boughs unto the sea, and her branches unto the river.
verses.verse_html: 11She sent out her boughs unto the sea, and her branches unto the river.

verses.text_plain: Why hast thou then broken down her hedges, so that all they which pass by the way do pluck her?
verses.verse_html: 12Why hast thou then broken down her hedges, so that all they which pass by the way do pluck her?

tokens.text: so that all they which pass

verses.text_plain: The boar out of the wood doth waste it, and the wild beast of the field doth devour it.
verses.verse_html: 13The boar out of the wood doth waste it, and the wild beast of the field doth devour it.

verses.text_plain: Return, we beseech thee, O God of hosts: look down from heaven, and behold, and visit this vine;
verses.verse_html: 14Return, we beseech thee, O God of hosts: look down from heaven, and behold, and visit this vine;

verses.text_plain: And the vineyard which thy right hand hath planted, and the branch that thou madest strong for thyself.
verses.verse_html: 15And the vineyard which thy right hand hath planted, and the branch that thou madest strong for thyself.

verses.text_plain: It is burned with fire, it is cut down: they perish at the rebuke of thy countenance.
verses.verse_html: 16It is burned with fire, it is cut down: they perish at the rebuke of thy countenance.

verses.text_plain: Let thy hand be upon the man of thy right hand, upon the son of man whom thou madest strong for thyself.
verses.verse_html: 17Let thy hand be upon the man of thy right hand, upon the son of man whom thou madest strong for thyself.

verses.text_plain: So will not we go back from thee: quicken us, and we will call upon thy name.
verses.verse_html: 18So will not we go back from thee: quicken us, and we will call upon thy name.

tokens.text: So will not we go back

verses.text_plain: Turn us again, O Lord God of hosts, cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.
verses.verse_html: 19Turn us again, O Lord God of hosts, cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.
